==English==

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈʤæspə/}}

===Etymology 1===
From Old French ''[[jaspre]]'', a variant of ''[[jaspe]]'' (modern French ''[[jaspe]]''), from Latin ''[[iaspis]]'', from Greek [[ἴασπις]], ultimately (via an oriental language) from Persian {{FAchar|[[یشپ]]}} (yašp).

====Noun====
{{en-noun|-}}
# ''(obsolete)'' Any bright-coloured kind of [[chalcedony]] apart from [[cornelian]].
# ''(Mineralogy):'' An opaque, impure variety of quartz, of red, yellow, and other dull colors, breaking with a smooth surface.
# [[jasper ware|Jasper ware]].

====See also====
*[[jasper ware]] <!--a delicate kind of earthenware invented by Josiah Wedgwood. It is usually white, but is capable of receiving color.-->
*[[jasper opal]]

===Etymology 2===
From the male personal name ''[[Jasper]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# ''(British, colloquial):'' A [[wasp]].
# (''US slang'') A person, a guy, especially seen as naïve or simple.
#:*'''1975''': I'm standing on the corner like a just-got-in-town '''jasper'''. — Tom Waits, ‘Nighthawk Postcards (From Easy Street)’

